com.ge.healthcare.dose.services.ruleengine

Class RuleProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ge.healthcare.dose.services.ruleengine.RuleProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public class RuleProcessor
extends Object
implements Runnable

    This Small implementation is a prototype for a simple RuleProcessor.

    It intends to evaluate JsonObject regarding some set of rules, and the execute the Rule processing if needed.

    basic usage : 

      RuleProcessor re = new RuleProcessor();  RuleContext rc = new RuleContext();  RuleSet rs = new RuleSet(“My-Own-RuleSet”);
    

    MyRule r = new MyRule();
rs.add(r);

re.setContext(rc);
re.add(rs);

JsonObject myObject = new JsonObject();

re.process("My-Own-RuleSet",myObject);
    ()

    Author:
    Frédéric Delormefrederic.delorme@ge.com

        The process method intends to evaluate all the activated RuleSet rule trigger and execute the corresponding rule process.

        Parameters:
        ruleSetName - the RuleSet name to be used for Rule processing on the object.
        objects - the object’s list to be evaluate regarding the RuleSet.
